<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="701" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/244</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Tiflis</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-26T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            26, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your telegram November 23 and previous telegrams. Please advise how
                                under circumstances you describe the financial support you propose
                                will not tend to encourage sectionalism or disruption of Russia or
                                civil war. Department cannot encourage tendencies in any of these
                                directions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>